comments.body: This failed again on https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/dec36166-c167-43a9-a858-a6ec824406d6
I suspect this error's a little different - someone put the wrong ark in the record as a placeholder prior to completing the record.
Yes, I should have mentioned that -- I reopened because I wasn't sure what to do about it! Does it just not require action?

Figgy is trying to update the ark in ezid but the ark isn't valid, so it's failing. Things we could do:

- not propagate arks that don't have `ark://` in them (don't pull them in from alma record) 
- ask users not to do it this way?
- allow the record to complete if the value that was in there has a failure, minting a new ark
  - there would be 2 arks, 1 would be bad forever.

How can we tell someone to fix this?
- Change the record in alma, pull in the metadata again, and then you'd be able to complete in figgy?
  - but we think maybe it won't override a local ark value once it's there.
- Change it in alma, delete the resource in figgy, then reingest it.
- Dev fix it.
